There is anything but Peruvian food in this restaurant.  The food is horrible.  The waitress was great and I wish we could say the same about the food.  The parihuela, which when made well, is a very tasty and somewhat creamy seafood soup. It was the worst parihuela we have ever had.  The estofado de pollo, which when made well is an amazing chicken stew.  This was the worst.  The chicken in it tasted like it was about to go bad, literally.  We told the waitress and she informed the cook. His answer was that the estofado was ok.  I think he felt we wanted our food for free or a discount, which is not the case.  We basically informed him so that they do not serve that stew to someone else.  I only took a bite of the stew and left it there.   It was inedible.  The chicken soup that the special came with, well, ramen tastes way better.  If you want to have Peruvian food, go somewhere  else, this place serves anything but Peruvian food.  I feel terrible because I am Peruvian and feel like Peru's food is not represented well by this restaurant.  Simply horrible.
